    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i hear that, but you're kind of brushing off the actual math. if you look at the studies that focus on the welfare cliff, it's pretty obvious that some of these policies actually punish people for trying to move up. it seems like you're leaning pretty hard into the idea that these programs are stabilizers, but isn't it more accurate to say they're creating a dependency that weakens the labor market?",
